======================================================================
COMBINATORIAL MEANING OF tr(A^4)
======================================================================

tr(A^k) = # closed walks of length k in the tournament
tr(A^4) = # ordered (i,j,k,l) with iв†’jв†’kв†’lв†’i

For tournaments, tr(A^4) counts:
  - 4-cycles: ordered directed 4-cycles (but tournaments have no
    directed 4-cycles! A tournament on 4 vertices has exactly one
    Hamiltonian cycle, which is a 4-cycle.)
  - Products of 2-walks: paths of length 4 returning to start
    include repeated vertices (e.g., iв†’jв†’iв†’jв†’i doesn't exist in
    tournaments since arcs are single-direction)

Wait: in a tournament, A[i][j] + A[j][i] = 1 for iв‰ j, A[i][i]=0.
So AВІ[i][j] = #{k : iв†’kв†’j}.
tr(AВІ) = ОЈ_i AВІ[i][i] = ОЈ_i #{k : iв†’kв†’i} = 0 (no 2-cycles in tournament)
Hmm, that gives 0, but we computed tr(AВІ) = 21 at p=7!

Ah: AВІ[i][j] = ОЈ_k A[i][k]*A[k][j] counts intermediate vertices
where iв†’k AND kв†’j. For i=j: AВІ[i][i] = #{k : A[i][k]=1 AND A[k][i]=1}
= #{k : iв†’k AND kв†’i} = 0 (tournament: exactly one direction)

p=7 Paley: AВІ[0][0] = 0, AВІ[1][1] = 0
tr(AВІ) = 0
But we said tr(AВІ) = ОЈО»ВІ = -0

Hmm, there's a discrepancy. Let me recheck...
AВІ[0][0] = 0 вЂ” this counts #{k : 0в†’k AND kв†’0}
Since 0в†’k means kв€€QR={1,2,4}, and kв†’0 means -kв€€QR, i.e., kв€€-QR={3,5,6}
So AВІ[0][0] = |QR в€© (-QR)| = |{1,2,4} в€© {3,5,6}| = 0

So tr(AВІ) = 0 for ANY tournament (no 2-cycles). вњ“

But we said ОЈ_k О»_kВІ = p*N_2 where N_2 = |{(s1,s2)в€€SВІ: s1+s2в‰Ў0}|.
At p=7: N_2 = 0 (tournament condition), so ОЈО»ВІ = 0.
But О»_0 = 3, so ОЈ_{kв‰ 0} О»_kВІ = -9. And tr(AВІ) = ОЈО»ВІ = 0.
Check: 9 + (-9) = 0 вњ“

So tr(AВІ) = 0 always. Then tr(AвЃґ) = ОЈ_{k=0}^{p-1} О»_kвЃґ.

p=7 Paley: tr(AвЃґ) = 84
  = 7 * (AвЃґ[0][0]) by circulant symmetry = 7 * 12
  AвЃґ[0][0] = # ways to walk 0в†’?в†’?в†’?в†’0 in 4 steps

  Direct count of walks 0в†’jв†’kв†’lв†’0: 12
  This includes walks with repeated vertices!

  Walk patterns by # distinct vertices:
    4 distinct vertices: 12 walks

So tr(AвЃґ) includes walks revisiting vertices.
4 distinct = directed 4-cycles through 0 (Г— 7 for all starts)
3 distinct = diamond-shaped walks (iв†’jв†’kв†’jв†’i type)
2 distinct = back-and-forth (impossible in tournament: no 2-cycles)

======================================================================
THE KEY FORMULA
======================================================================

At p=7: H = (462 - tr(AвЃґ))/2

This means: MINIMIZING tr(AвЃґ) = MAXIMIZING H.

tr(AвЃґ) = ОЈ |О»_k|вЃґВ·cos(4В·arg(О»_k)) + |О»_0|вЃґ
        = ((p-1)/2)вЃґ + ОЈ_{kв‰ 0} Re(О»_kвЃґ)

For Paley: all |О»_k| = в€љ((p+1)/4), all phases = В±arctan(в€љp)
  tr(AвЃґ) = ((p-1)/2)вЃґ + (p-1)В·((p+1)/4)ВІ В· cos(4В·arctan(в€љp))

For flat spectrum at p=7:
  О»_k = -1/2 В± iв€љ7/2, |О»|ВІ = 2, |О»|вЃґ = 4
  arg(О») в‰€ В±1.9322 rad
  4В·arg в‰€ В±7.7288 в†’ cos(7.7288) в‰€ cos(7.7288-2ПЂ) в‰€ cos(1.446) в‰€ 0.1245
  ОЈ Re(О»вЃґ) = 6 Г— 4 Г— 0.125000 = 3.0000
  tr(AвЃґ) = 81 + 3.0000 = 84.0000
  Expected: 84. Check: True

======================================================================
SCHUR CONVEXITY: WHY FLAT MINIMIZES tr(AвЃґ)
======================================================================

For p в‰Ў 3 mod 4, all eigenvalues satisfy Re(О»_k) = -1/2 (universal).
So О»_k = -1/2 + iВ·y_k where y_k are the imaginary parts.

Parseval: ОЈ |О»_k|ВІ = ОЈ (1/4 + y_kВІ) = (p-1)(p+1)/4
  в†’ ОЈ y_kВІ = (p-1)(p+1)/4 - (p-1)/4 = (p-1)p/4

Now: О»_kвЃґ = (-1/2 + iy_k)вЃґ
  = (1/2 - iy_k)вЃґ ... wait: (-1/2 + iy)вЃґ = ((-1+2iy)/2)вЃґ = (1-2iy)вЃґ/16
  = (1 - 8iy - 24yВІ + 32iyВі + 16yвЃґ)/16... let me compute properly.

  (-1/2 + iy)вЃґ = y**4 + 2*I*y**3 - 3*y**2/2 - I*y/2 + 1/16
  Re part: re(y)**4 - 6*re(y)**2*im(y)**2 - 6*re(y)**2*im(y) - 3*re(y)**2/2 + im(y)**4 + 2*im(y)**3 + 3*im(y)**2/2 + im(y)/2 + 1/16

  Re((-1/2 + iy)вЃґ) = 1/16 - 3yВІ/2 + yвЃґ

  ОЈ_{kв‰ 0} Re(О»_kвЃґ) = ОЈ (1/16 - 3y_kВІ/2 + y_kвЃґ)
                     = (p-1)/16 - 3/2В·ОЈy_kВІ + ОЈy_kвЃґ
                     = (p-1)/16 - 3(p-1)p/8 + ОЈy_kвЃґ

  So tr(AвЃґ) = ((p-1)/2)вЃґ + (p-1)/16 - 3(p-1)p/8 + ОЈy_kвЃґ
            = CONSTANT + ОЈy_kвЃґ

  H = (Cв‚Ѓ - tr(AвЃґ))/2 = (Cв‚‚ - ОЈy_kвЃґ)/2

  THEREFORE: H is maximized вџє ОЈy_kвЃґ is minimized
  вџє all y_kВІ are equal (by convexity of xВІ)
  вџє FLAT SPECTRUM (Paley)

  THIS IS THE COMPLETE PROOF OF STEP B AT p=7!

